  <li id="comment-41611" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="http://swimming-with-sharks.blogspot.com" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Christine</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2013/12/approximately-a-soup/#comment-41611"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2013-12-06T21:04:36-05:00">Friday, December 6, 2013 at 9:04 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I love Marcella and make a similar smothered cabbage &#8211; only usually I just mix it with cooked orzo for an even lazier meal.  Also, I&#39;ve never cooked it for quite that long, usually closer to 45 minutes or whenever it gets meltingly tender.  I&#39;ll have to try the extra time and see if the difference makes it worth it.  And I&#39;ll have to try with some garlic added. Usually I just use the onion, carmelize the onion for a bit, throw in the shredded cabbage, lid it and let it cook for about a half hour or so on low that way with maybe a few spoonfuls of water added and a generous pinch of salt and fresh ground pepper.  Take off the lid, raise heat and carmelize the mixture some more, add in small cooked pasta, add cheese and devour.  </p>
<p>Sometimes, I just eat the entire head of cabbage cooked this way without the pasta.</p>
    </div>

      </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-41691" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
