  <li id="comment-41653" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/07408738427519826428" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Jessica</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2013/12/approximately-a-soup/#comment-41653"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2014-01-14T17:57:58-05:00">Tuesday, January 14, 2014 at 5:57 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Just wanted to say thanks for posting this recipe. It&#39;s not glamorous, but it&#39;s wonderfully delicious. We&#39;ve made it 3 times in 3 weeks, and I keep hoping to put some in the freezer but the pot gets emptied every time. We&#39;ve also added in kale and brussel sprouts when our cabbage didn&#39;t look like enough, and both additions were delicious! Brown rice instead of the arborio works just as well, too, since the long slow simmer helps break it down. For a vegan version, we skipped the cheese but drizzled a little truffle oil on top of each serving. AMAZING!! Thank you for brining us this wonder!</p>
    </div>

